===Public Key Format===

When CHECKSIG opcodes pop a non-empty pubkey from the stack, the verifier assumes the pubkey byte vector has the following structure:

<pre>
flag || pubkey
</pre>

… where <code>flag</code> is a byte corresponding to a standardized signature verification algorithm flag.

Two verification algorithm flags are defined in this BIP:

* <code>0x01</code>: SHRINCS.
* <code>0x02</code>: BIP340<ref>By using <code>0x02</code> as the algorithm flag for a BIP340 pubkey, the key appears the same as it would if we took the full lifted secp256k1 curve point and encoded it with the standard compressed point encoding format.</ref>.

Any pubkey which uses an unidentified algorithm flag prefix is essentially an “anyone-can-spend” public key, because verifiers will auto-succeed when they validate signatures against that key. This allows future BIPs to define new verification algorithms using a soft-fork.

We now define the signature verification algorithms for these two flags.


====Signature Format====

SHRINCS signatures can exceed the 520-byte limit for stack elements. Therefore, the new tapscript version <code>0xC2</code> introduced in this BIP lifts the 520 byte limit on stack element sizes to 6000 bytes.

SHRINCS signatures may either use the stateful or the stateless path inside the key, and either is equally valid. Stateless SHRINCS signatures are very large, but always a constant size of 5776 bytes. Stateful SHRINCS signatures are much shorter, but are of variable size, to a maximum of XXX bytes.

